INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('33', '19', '1', '1997-01-04', 'Brewed', '1.100', '60.0', 'Mash in @122F in 9 gallons water. Let rest for 20 mins and bringto 150F. Rest for 1 hour and boost to 158F for 20 mins. Mash outat168F. Drain tun to collect 7 gallon of 1073 wort.  Boil to 4.5 gallons. Chill and make up volume to 5.5 gallons with baby.||Baby:Fill tun back up with 8 gallons sparge water. Add 1 lb crystal,2.5 pale and .25 victory to mash after mashing in a bucket at 144Ffor 30 mins.  Boost to 168F and drain tun to kettle. Add 40 gmperle and boil for 30 mins. Move to boil kettle on top of spent hops and boil for 30 mins. Add 25 gm cascade at 15 and 0 mins. S.G.@1048 for 5 gallons. Sprayed on top of 1056 yeast cake|1/4 - bothare fermenting.|1/28 = Kegged baby @ 1008. Not bad. Dry hop with10 gm galena, 10 gm chinook, 10 gm centeninal.|2/7 Kegged Gnarley with 20 gm galena, 20 gm chinook and 20 gm cascade. Bottled237oz coke bottles.|3/2 Sampled keg. Smooth and bitter with a mintyalcoholic aftertaste. Very clear, morning piss yellow.||Big Tooth is smooth and bitter.');
