INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('35', '20', '1', '1997-04-05', 'Brewed', '1.103', '0.0', 'Attempted to mash at 135F and then boost to 145F. The mash however stuck like a pig! Next time I should mini-mash the oats with barley with an extended protein rest and them bring the mess up toboiling and then add to the main mash. I did manage after resetting the bed twice to get the mash up to 160+ and then lauter. I collected about 7 gallons of 1085 wort which was boiled to 4.75 gallons of 1103.||Second mash I added 5 lbs of pale malt, 1 lb crystal 40 and 1 lb munich. Brought temp to 150\'s for 30 mins and mashed out to 168F. Collect 7.5 gallons which got boiled down to about5.75 gallons of 1070. The hop sch was 80 gms of perle (70 mins),25 gm cascade (30 mins), spent hops (15 mins) , then 25 gms ofcascade leaf (knock out).||4/28 Racked big to 2ndary. Pitched Pasteur Champagne dry yeast.|5/1 Kegged Baby with 10 gm Chinook, 10gmCascade, 10 gm Super Alpha, 30 gm Styrian Goldings');
