INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('46', '25', '1', '1997-11-08', 'Brewed', '1.063', '68.0', '11/8 Mashed Munich in 2.5 gallons water @ 150 for 10 mins. Boostto boiling over 5 mins and boil for 15 mins. Messed up and mashedthe remainer of the grain and hit 167F. Let drain to a vessel tocollect about 7 gallons of wort and let sit overnight.|Next morningput wort back to mash tun and mash in 10 more lbs of grain at148F for 30 mins. Boost to 154F and let rest for 1 hour. Droppedintothe 140\'s. Boost to 168F and drain. Sparge to 11 gallons and boil. Add water to 12 gallons.  Pitched large starter from RedBell @68F. Left in garage.|11/9 24 hours later temp @ 56F and activelyfermenting.|11/10 A.M. @ 54F S.G. in hydrojar @ 1046.|11/11P.M.@50F |11/12 P.M. @ 48F|11/13 P.M. @ 43F S.G. @ 1030|11/15 Movedunto front porch. @ 42F.|11/16 @ 45F|11/29 Kegged and pressured to10 lbs.|12/20 Bottled 5 gallons w/50 gm Cane sugar for 2.7 vols.Beer had been in garage lagering @ 38F in a keg.||11/8/98 - Score 1st w/39.5 in Novembeerfest in Seattle. MCAB qualifier.|Last four hops were mixed and added at 10, 4, nd 0 mins.|Friday evening, I was attempting to do a small decoction on a batch of|Fest beer I was making. I mashed 10 lbs of munich in 2.5 gallons at 150F|for 15 mins, boosted to 158F for 15 mins and boiledfor 15mins. This|was added to the rest of my mash water (6.5 gallons) at 145F and I then|added the rest of the grain bill consisting of12.5 lbs 2 row, 2.5 lbs|crystal and recirculated. Unfortunately,I hit 170F. With the mash being|thin already I was reluctanttoadd water to cool it down. So I put then|lid on the tun and leftit.||The next morning, I drained the mash tun and collected thefirst|runnings. I then emptied the spent grains from the tun, added back the|first runnings (6.5 gallons) and heated to 158F. Icrushed another 10|lbs of 2 row and added this to the mash to rest at148F for 30 mins. I|then boosted to 154F for an hour and mashedout at 170F. I then sparged|the grain bed with 5 galons of waterand continued. I got a O.G. of 1063|for 12 gallons for wort out of35 lbs of grain, basically a low sparge|beer.||My questions arewhat kind of sugars will make up the wort? The initial|rest at 170Ffor most of the grain bill will have produced plenty of|dextrins, but the additional mashing at 148F should have reduced these.|Hopefully there were enough enzymes in the second mashing and themash|wasn\'t too thin to have some reduction.');
INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('47', '26', '1', '1997-11-29', 'Brewed', '0.000', '0.0', 'Mash in @ 154F. Drop to 131F. Boost to 154F for 20 mins.|Fermenton porch between 45-50F.|12/17 50F @ 1022 SG|1/21 @ 1022. Keg?? orBottle??||Hugh Baird Malt');
INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('48', '27', '1', '1996-11-30', 'Brewed', '1.058', '0.0', 'mash in 10 Gallons water @ 166F, rest @ 152 for 1.5 hours. Mash out @ 168, lauter to 15 gallons. Boil and add extra run-off as required. Boil 1.5 hours and add finish hops and chill.|12/6 S.G. @1.048|12/14 @ 1.032|12/15 racked to corney kegs.|1/9 racked to kegs.||Starter was wyeast pack pitched into 3/4 gallon of last week extra-runoff+kettle dregs. Fermented at 60F start and lowered to 45Fby the end of the week.|12/7 Tastes great from starter which wasfermented and clear.');
INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('49', '28', '1', '1998-11-20', 'Brewed', '1.060', '0.0', 'Mash in @ 135F. Mini-mash 8 lbs in enough water to create a thickmash. Boost to 155F over 20 mins. Rest in the 150\'s for 15 mins,boost to boiling over 15 mins and boil for 15 mins. Add back tomain mash to hit 141F. Boost to 151F over 20 mins. Rest at 151F for 30 mins. Boost to 158F for 10 mins and drain. Sparge with 6 gallons of water and collect final volume of 14 gallons. Boil for 120 mins. Chill. Add yeast to kettle & recirc some more. Trans tocarboys at 64F.|11/20 - 12 hours later temp in high 50\'s and fermenting nicely.|12/2 - kegged 5 gallons. Nice & clear. Thinish, butgood. Stuck in PJ\'s freezer.|12/28 - removed from freezer. let warm to room temp to release excess CO2 and then bottle.');
INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('50', '28', '1', '1998-12-04', 'Packaged', '1.016', '0.0', '');
INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('51', '29', '1', '1998-12-03', 'Brewed', '1.058', '0.0', 'Mash in 20 lbs into 7 gallons water to hit 135F. Mash 5 lbs into3gallons of water. Wait 5 mins and drain most of the liquid backto the main mash. Heat mini-mash to 158F and rest for 20 mins. Boil for 20 mins. Return to main mash to hit 140F. Boost to 151F.Rest for 20 mins. Boost to 151F. Rest and boost to 160F. Drain. Batch sparge. Boil for 90 mins. Chill to 72F and add yeast to kettle.Spray to carboys at 62F.|12/10 - Fermentation temp was all overplace due to heat wave. Kept temp down by putting carboys in tubswith 15 gallons of water each. Added frozen gallon jugs to keeptemp down. Probably averaged about 57F, with a high of 61F. Currently temp is 49F. SG @ 1019|12/12 - Racked 5 gallons. Tastes veryclean and doesn\'t seem to have been affected by temp swings.|12/26 - SG @ 1019|12/29 - Cane- 93 Grams in 5 Gallons for 2.65 vols@ 62F|1/11 - Cane - 2/3 cup in 6 gallons.');
