INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('63', '36', '1', '1999-02-06', 'Brewed', '1.072', '0.0', 'Mash in the 140\'s, boost to 154F for 90 mins adding heat as necessary. Drain to collect 6 gallons run off. Batch sparge and collect 6 more gallons. Fly sparge 10 quarts more thru grain bed and add to kettle. Boil for 90+mins. Add honey with 6 mins left to go.Chill and add water to 15 gallons. Add yeast to kettle. It was alittle warm (85?).|2/7 - PM and just starting to get krausen.|2/8 -AM full high krausen @ 70F. PM @ 65F.|2/10 - Been between 65 & 70F. SG @ 1040. Very piney.|2/12 - Krausen dropping.|2/13 - Rackedtwo 5 gallons carboys and dry hopped with 20 gm Chinook, 20 gm Styrian Goldings each steamed for 10 min.|2/23 - bottled un-dry-hopped sg @ 1014: Cane- 50 Grams In 3.25 Gallons For 2.3 Vols @ 55.0f|3/2 - Bottled dry-hopped: Cane- 78 Grams in 5.0 Gallons for2.3vols @ 55.0FF');
