INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('90', '51', '1', '1998-08-16', 'Brewed', '1.073', '0.0', 'picked 5 quart bags full of mulberrys and froze. Fill blender with berrys and topped up with water to the 44 oz line. Each bag filled the blender perfectly. Cut up the nectarines and plums and blended them as well. Used a total of 2 gallons of water to blend the fruit. After blending the SG of the fruit/water was 1018 @ 66F. Wanting a higher fruit gravity, I added 2 quarts of frozen blueberrys to the mix. This yielded a gravity of 1020 @ 80F. Added 5lbs honey and heated to 160F and covered. This sat for 20 hours until 80F and then I pitched the yeast. The gravity was 1073.|9/2-SG @ 1000 and cloudy. Very tart and tannic with a berry finish. Much like a red wine.|1/31/98 - tart and very lambic like.|1/23/99-Put entire carboy outside to freeze. Rack off the unfrozen portion.');
