INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('103', '58', '1', '1999-01-30', 'Brewed', '1.052', '0.0', 'Mash 5.5 plbs polenta and 5 lbs malt in 2.5 gallons water. Heat from 100F to 154F over 20 mins and rest for 20 mins. Boil for 1 hour. Mash in rest of grains at 148F. Add corn mush to main mash and rest at 152F. Recirc and try to keep in the low 150\'s. Mash didnot want to recirc and I had to keep stirring. This made keepingtemps tough. Drain tun to kettle over 30 mins. Add batch spargewater and stir. Recirc for a couple of minutes to clear and thenlet sit for 15 mins. Drain. Added saaz to kettle before first runnings and then added chinook when full boil started. During boiladdleft over sparged wort to keep volume at top. While chilling, add water to keep volume at top. Add yeast while in 70\'s and transfer to carboys at 66F. Left on porch overnight and was at 38F in the morning. Move inside and then to cold box when at 50F.|2/1- ferment been and is at 50F.|2/4 - up to 54F.|2/8 - @ 52F|2/10 @ 52F& 1013|2/23 -Cane- 70 Grams in 4.0 Gallons for 2.54 vols @ 50.0F|3/27 - 2nd place in hops-bops.|4/19 - Cane- 110 Grams in 6.0 Gallons for 2.5 vols @ 56.0F||Mixed yeast from two different batches of bo pils.|The yeast character from the Bavarian lager is out of style. (perhaps not w/39.5 score in HOPS-BOPS!)');
