INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('130', '72', '1', '1997-10-02', 'Brewed', '0.000', '0.0', 'Mash in 172F water. Rested @ 161F so added cold water to rest @ 158F. By end of 80 mins it was @ 154F. Batch sparged. Added FWH of1 plug of EKG.  15 min hops were plugs and final was 1 plug andrest pellets.|Pitched yeast @ 71F in sanke.|Next morning temp @ 64F and smelling fruity. Later that afternoon @ 62F and 1043 sg. Ihope the temp don\'t keep dropping. Covered with sleeping bag andtemp held at 62F.|10/21 Gravity at 1025, temp @ 59F. Rack to carboys and bring inside. There was a hell of a lot of yeast in thefermenter and it should have finished. Take 3 tablespoons from thebottom and make a fresh starter. Add when it hits krausen. This didn\'t seem to help.');
