INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('150', '84', '1', '1997-01-25', 'Brewed', '1.052', '70.0', 'Mash in 10 gallons of 165F water to rest @ 156F for 1 hour. Mashout at 168F and drain tun (1.5 hours). Refill with 8 gallons of sparge water @ 150F and recirc and heat until @ 168F.  Added bitterhops and began to boil the collected volume. When the kettle begins to boil, let mash tun drain into the kettle slow enough to maintain boil. Collect about 13.5 gallons. After one hour from thestart of the boil, begin rest of the hopping. Chill and pitch German Ale and American Ale @ 70F.|1/26 krausen rising, temp dropping. @ 60F.|1/27 Germany is storming the airlock! Gobs of yeast comming through. This is a nice yeast for 60F.|1/29 Changed airlockonGermany. Tasted ok, smelly yeasty. America has nice one-two inchkrausen on top.|2/1 Kegged Germany and dry hopped with 30 gmsMt.Hood.');
