INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('157', '87', '1', '1998-01-03', 'Brewed', '1.066', '0.0', 'Mash in @ 140F for 20 mins. Boost to 153F for 60 mins. Sparge boil for 90 mins. Chill to 64F. Pitch yeast from bottom of secondaries.|1/4 - Lager @ 62F|1/5 - Lager @ 58 w/no activity. Pitch moreyeast in the late evening.|1/6 - Lager fermenting @ 55F|1/7 - Lager Temp up to 60! Spring has Sprung. Put in fridge @ 50F|1/10 - Lager @ 52F.|1/12 - Move lager out of fridge.|1/13 - Ale @ 1020 andvery bitter. This could be on target. Lager @ 1032 & tastes confusing.|1/16 - Lager @ 46F & 1028|1/1? - Temp down to 42F on porch.|1/21 - L@ 44F & 1024. Taste is still confusing. Sulfur/yeasty.Ale & 1017. Wow! Bitter, not malty, still yeasty.|1/24 Transferalefor yeast cake.|1/26 Move ale to porch to crash chill.|1/29Lager@ 52F & 1018. Woozie! Nice Bitter beer. Still hazy.|2/4 Keggedlager @ 1017. Not so bitter any more.|2/8 - bottled 5 gallons||The Aroma/Flavor hop, Hopbreath, consists of equal parts of Chinook (10.3), Columbus (12.4), Tettnang (4.7), and Spalt (5.0)');
