INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('197', '109', '1', '1997-02-01', 'Brewed', '1.056', '60.0', 'mash in 10 gallons @ 166F to rest @ 156F for 1 hour. Empty tun and begin boil. Add sparge water to 10 gallons and recirc and heatto 168F. Slowly drain tun to kettle while maintaining a boil. Boilfor total of 100 mins. Hop according to schedule. Chill to 68F.|2/8 kegged 5 gallons w/60 gm cascade.|2/23 - Bottled  2 gallonswith 34 grams corn sugar for 2.2 volumes.||5 hour brew day. This yeast rules! Beautify head and fermented out by wednesday evening.|Not a great IPA yeast but interesting.');
