INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('217', '119', '1', '1996-12-21', 'Brewed', '1.057', '0.0', 'Mash in @ 160F for 1 hour. Emptied tun and refilled with about 3gallons water. Added first hops to kettle. Recirc water in tun anddrian after 15 mins. Added 5 gallons water to tun and recirc. Bring collected volume to a boil (30 mins) and begin to drain tuntokettle very slowly whilst boiling. Runnings at 1018. Cut off sparge when kettle volume up to about 13.5 gallons. By this time thewort had been boiling for about 45 mins. Followed rest of thehopschedule and chilled. Racked off 5.5 gallons into one fermenterand pitched Irish Ale from bottom of secondary of stout. Ended upwith about 4 gallons in other fermenter so added 2 gallons of 1018runoff to kettle and brought to a boil for 5 mins, chilledandadded to fermenter to end with about 6.5 gallons of unknown gravity.Pitch 1056 from Barley wine.|12/23 No activity in 1056, so kegged porter and racked on top of yeast. Other fermenter is lookinggood.|12/24 Everything looks good with 1056 batch. Irish guy is slowing down and looks close to done.|12/26 Irish is good and hoppy.@ 1022 @ 62F.|12/28 Kegged Irish w/2 oz cascade pellets.||1/10 first sample from the keg is delicious... Got to make more.');
