INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('301', '169', '1', '1998-01-24', 'Brewed', '1.050', '0.0', '1/24 Mash @ 138 for 10 mins. Bring to 154 over 20 mins & rest for60 mins. Dual batch sparge & boil. Add honey just before knockout. Chill & top up kettle with excess sparge water.|Ferment 6.5 gallons w/Notttingham, 5 gallons with NW ESB and 3.25 gallons w/1007.|1/26 - 1007 @ 58F & Rocky head forming. All other ferments appear normal with Nott bubbling about 3 times faster then NW ESB.|1/29 NW done @ 1010. Has a bitter aftertaste but smooth. Add 2 pints strawberry blended in 1 pint water heated to boiling, puried and cooled to room temp to Nott.|2/4 German @ 1018 & weizen like,move to warmer loc. Strawberry @ 1008 & not so strawberry.|2/8 -Bottled Strawberry & Nottingham to 2.7 volumes. Strawberry may comeout high, there was a lot of volume left behind as sediment.|3/23 - Bottled German. Crystal Clear. 74 grams sucrose for 2.75 volumes.||German ferment below 58F.');
