INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('335', '190', '1', '2000-03-31', 'Brewed', '1.105', '0.0', 'Mash in @ 148F for 15 mins. Boost to 154F for 30 mins. Boost to 168F over 10 mins. Drain. Batch sparge. Collect 15 gallons. Drainoff 2.5 gallons into another pot. Boil for 120 mins. Pitched chimay yeast into 6 gallons and 3944 to 5 gallons. Added a wee bit ofthe chimay yeast to the 5 gallon for the hell of it.|6/3 - 3rd place in 2000 Buzz-Off||Strong Dark:|2.5 gallons was boiled seperate with 3.3 lbs of NW Gold extract, 20 gms of Hallertau, 20 gms chinook, 1.5 cups of cane sugar, 5 rosehips, some grains of paradise and 1 cup of raisins. Pitched mixed yeast to it. SG of 1.105.Next week I added about a gallon of tripel on top. |05/05 - SG @1022|06/17 - SG @ 1012! @ 70F');
