INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('337', '191', '1', '1996-10-26', 'Brewed', '1.050', '0.0', 'Mash in 110, let sit for 15 hours. Temp dropped to 95F. Big stink! Major problems with the flow. Had to reset bed several times. Boost to 128 for 30 mins. Stuck again. Boost to 148 for 45 mins. Stuck again. Set up lauter tun to gravity into the kettle and left. 6 hours later all had drained. Boiled 5 gallons water and addedto the bed. Left sit for 1 hour and opened the valve to drain into kettle again. In the morning, not lautered so began boil of what was in kettle and started the lauter going and added to kettleas it came out. Boiled kettle volume down to 11 gallons over 4 hours. Add  .5 oz Curacao w/Centeninal @ 60 mins. Add .5 oz Curacao, .5 oz Sweet Orange w/Cascade @ 30 mins. Add .5 oz Curacao, .5oz Sweet Orange, 5 gm Coriander w/Cascade/Saaz @ 15 mins. Add 5 gmCoriander w/Saaz @ 0 mins. Chilled and added volume back to 11gallons. Pitch yeast (which smelled fantasic) @74F  11/2 59F/1032,Place carboys next to radiator and got temp up to 70F. Swirledcarboys and krausen rose up again.  11/7 73F/1017. 11/8 Rack 5 gallons for yeast for mead. 11/11 add 1.5 gms crushed coriander to5 gallons and 2 gms coriander in boiled water to 6 gallon secondary.|||This brew was started thursday evening and finished saturday afternoon. Almost puked from sucking up a mouthful of lactic grains when trying to unstick a stuck mash.');
INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('338', '191', '1', '1996-11-09', 'Packaged', '1.011', '0.0', '');
INSERT INTO `recipedates` VALUES ('339', '192', '1', '1997-11-14', 'Brewed', '1.044', '0.0', 'Bake yams in oven for 150 mins, and blend into 3 qts water. Add 2.5 lbs crushed wheat malt and rest at 91F. Slowly bring to 152F and rest for 2 hours dropping into the 130\'s. Bring to a boil andcover till morning.|11/15 Mash in remaining grain bill in 8 gallons of water to rest @ 154F. Meanwhile bring yams up to 154F and add to  the tun. Rest between 150-156F for an hour boosting as needed. Drain and refill sparge with 185F water. Boil with all bittering hops added FWH for 90 mins. Chill to 70F and pitch NW Ale from bottom of Load king and 2 qts fermenting wort sucked from thebottom of the primary of Bob Marzen.');
